1000002600870@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Plural direct objects end with the combination ⌊/-ojn/⌋ (pronounced to rhyme with "coin"): That is, ⌊/-o/⌋ for a noun, plus ⌊/-j/⌋ for plural, plus ⌊/-n/⌋ for direct object.@@@@1@28@@oe@26-8-2013
